				</ukm:Metadata><Secondary><Schedules RestrictExtent="E+W+S" RestrictStartDate="2026-04-06"><Schedule DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2013/376/schedule/5" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/schedule/5" NumberOfProvisions="13" id="schedule-5" RestrictStartDate="2022-04-11"><Number>SCHEDULE 5</Number><TitleBlock><Title>Housing costs element for owner-occupiers</Title></TitleBlock><ScheduleBody><Part DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2013/376/schedule/5/part/2" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/schedule/5/part/2" NumberOfProvisions="1" id="schedule-5-part-2" RestrictStartDate="2013-04-29"><Number><Strong>PART 2</Strong></Number><Title>Exception to inclusion of housing costs element</Title><P1group RestrictStartDate="2013-04-29"><Title>No housing costs element where owner-occupier has any earned income</Title><P1 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2013/376/schedule/5/paragraph/4" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/schedule/5/paragraph/4" id="schedule-5-paragraph-4"><Pnumber>4</Pnumber><P1para><P2 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2013/376/schedule/5/paragraph/4/1" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/schedule/5/paragraph/4/1" id="schedule-5-paragraph-4-1"><Pnumber>1</Pnumber><P2para><Text>Section 11(1) of the Act (housing costs) does not apply to any owner-occupier in relation to an assessment period where—</Text><P3 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2013/376/schedule/5/paragraph/4/1/a" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/schedule/5/paragraph/4/1/a" id="schedule-5-paragraph-4-1-a"><Pnumber>a</Pnumber><P3para><Text>the owner-occupier has any earned income; or</Text></P3para></P3><P3 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2013/376/schedule/5/paragraph/4/1/b" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/schedule/5/paragraph/4/1/b" id="schedule-5-paragraph-4-1-b"><Pnumber>b</Pnumber><P3para><Text>if the owner-occupier is a member of a couple, either member of the couple has any earned income.</Text></P3para></P3></P2para></P2><P2 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2013/376/schedule/5/paragraph/4/2" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/schedule/5/paragraph/4/2" id="schedule-5-paragraph-4-2"><Pnumber>2</Pnumber><P2para><Text>Sub-paragraph (1) applies irrespective of the nature of the work engaged in, its duration or the amount of the earned income.</Text></P2para></P2><P2 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2013/376/schedule/5/paragraph/4/3" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/schedule/5/paragraph/4/3" id="schedule-5-paragraph-4-3"><Pnumber>3</Pnumber><P2para><Text>Nothing in this paragraph prevents an amount calculated under Schedule 4 from being included in the award of any claimant who falls within regulation 26(4) to (6) (shared ownership).</Text></P2para></P2></P1para></P1></P1group></Part></ScheduleBody></Schedule></Schedules></Secondary></Legislation>